Mukesh Ambani Gets Bank of America Shares as Fees, Express Says

-- B y   R a k t e e m   K a t a k e y
-- 
2011-04-13T03:56:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/mukesh-ambani-gets-bank-of-america-shares-as-fees-express-says.html
Bank of America Corp. (BAC)  has given
 Reliance Industries Ltd. (RIL)  Chairman Mukesh Ambani shares valued at
1.1 million rupees ($24,700) as fees for being a director at the
U.S. bank, the Indian Express reported.  Ambani may get 10 million rupees in cash and stocks as
annual director fees, the newspaper said, without saying where
it got the information.  Manoj Warrier, a spokesman for Reliance Industries,
declined to comment when reached on his mobile phone today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rakteem Katakey in New Delhi at 
 rkatakey@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Amit Prakash at   aprakash1@bloomberg.net . 